Ecosystem

rawssg is built entirely in Rust. Its architecture is modular and separated by responsibility.

Each part of the system is released as a separate library to maintain flexibility, maintainability, and long-term scalability.

Ecosystem structure:

1. Core Engine
Responsible for the core parsing, build, and orchestration processes.

2. UI/UX Layer
Manages user interactions and the tool experience.

3. Template System
Manages the templating system to ensure flexibility and independent development.

Libraries released in the rawssg ecosystem:

rawssg lib
The main rawssg core engine.
Repository:
[https://github.com/neuxdotdev/librawssg.git](https://github.com/neuxdotdev/librawssg.git)

rawssg-templates
The official collection of templates for rawssg.
Repository:
[https://github.com/neuxdotdev/rawssg-templates.git](https://github.com/neuxdotdev/rawssg-templates.git)

uirawssg
UI and UX components for rawssg.
Repository:
[https://github.com/neuxdotdev/uirawssg.git](https://github.com/neuxdotdev/uirawssg.git)

Conclusion

rawssg is a constantly evolving project. Its focus is not on being the most widely used, but on being the one with the clearest direction and purpose.

Simplicity does not mean a lack of features. Simplicity is a design decision.
